cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this study, harness, or data, please cite it as below."
title: "Fast and Faithful? Distilling an 8B Reasoning Teacher into a Sub-1B On-Device Student for Structured News Enrichment"
authors:
  - family-names: Chaganti
    given-names: Vinay Kumar
    email: cvk.atreya@gmail.com
type: software
repository-code: "https://github.com/socraticsurge/distill-locally"
license: MIT
date-released: 2026-07-02
keywords:
  - knowledge distillation
  - small language models
  - LLM-as-judge
  - on-device inference
  - summarization
  - structured output
abstract: >-
  Pre-specified (frozen-before-scoring) study distilling DeepSeek-R1:8b into Qwen3-0.6B for structured
  RSS-article enrichment (free-text summary, five categorical labels, open-set
  topics), evaluated per sub-task against two non-distillation controls with a
  blinded two-judge LLM panel graded on full article text. Reports gap-closure
  toward the teacher, a localized short-source faithfulness regression, and a
  per-field engine assignment. Reproduces offline from a cached judge panel.
